{
  "texts": [
    "Let Assumptions 4.1, 4.2, 4.3, 4.4(i)(ii)(iv), and 4.5(i)(ii)(iv) be satisfied.",
    "Then, the value function U (= V) defined in (3.2) is a B-continuous viscosity solution of (3.3) in the sense of Definition 7.8.",
    "The proof is a straightforward modification of the one of [52, Theorem 3.66] using Lemma 7.7 in place of [52, Proposition 1.166].",
    "We remark that in the proof we can assume that the controls a(•) are bounded (recall Proposition 6.3) and hence the solutions of the state equation have moments of any order.",
    "□ Lemma 7.10."
  ]
}